caption: Laid back BBQ place.  Live music.  Huge ribs. Nice selection of drinks and beers.  Full bar as well.
I love 1-off BBQ joints, and in Texas that goes double.
Wait staff great, portions are great now time for karaoke!!!

Amazing eating experience.  Having travelled the world over and the majority of southern BBQ states.  Oak'd is my newest favorite.  The food is amazing and portions are generous- the cost warrants the flavor.  The staff is friendly, the entire location is clean.  i love it, and pick up from there often.
Had the waygu brisket, waygu burnt ends, waygu cheese sausage and bacon burnt ends. My favorites were the brisket and the sausage; wife's were the waygu burnt ends and the bacon burnt ends.

Great service and fun environment for the family to enjoy BBQ but it is also much more than that. There is a bar. Yes a full service bar. And a dessert bar full of pies and cookies. There is patio seating with corn holes. And most …
Sunday 21March at 653PM the freaking BEEF RIBS and BURNT ENDS ARE OUTSTANDING GOOD GOOD GOOD. You won’t be disappointed.

Oak'd is one of those bbq places you love to see. Casual & authentic southern vibes channeled into good old fashioned meats. I stopped in and ordered a sandwich called the governor, which was insanely large. I loved every bite, I'm sure I'll be back.
This is great the barbecue ribs is the top the sides very good and as Victoria would say yummy delicious barbecue ribs you get alot for the price

A defining trait of oak is listed as “dark majestic beauty.” Dark majestic beauty would be understating how incredible every single piece of meat I ate at this restaurant was.  If you’ve ever enjoyed a piece of sausage, it was likely …

This bbq place was amazing! The environment, food, staff, sides all incredible. We even had the chance to talk to Nathan about how he makes the bbq everyday! Such a good experience. If I could eat the jalapeño and cheddar sausages all day I would!

2nd visit= sliced beef was like gristle, beans way over-cooked & tasteless, still waiting for home fries that are actually cooked before served instead of warmed up fries. Overall meal was over priced for quality of food given
Excellent food, excellent service!

I’ll start with the good...atmosphere, corn hole and some of the food. We tried it bc my wife and I are fans of the owners. The food: good-Mac and cheese, jalapeño and cheese sausage, tea, and chocolate chip cookie. The not so good: potato …
Wow...went for lunch with a friend. Great food. Burtnt ends where just right, smoked turkey and brisket. Roasted Brussels sprouts. Excellent service too.

The ordering process was slow and disorganized. The BBQ was ok but the sides weren’t great (they were out of baked potatoes - we ordered steak fries and sweet cole slaw... both were mostly completely left behind.  Lastly the sauce (it’s all …

First time visiting this place. I was really impressed. We only do meats...so we picked up ribs, brisket, burnt ends and sausage. Everything was delicious, flavorful and tender. Leftovers were even better!
Very pricey for mediocre bbq. The brisket lacked flavor, had too much fatty chunks or wasn’t cooked properly. Ribs were meh as well. The Mac and cheese was good. Wouldn’t come here again though.
Very tasty plenty of food nice environment.
This place is amazing well worth the price tag and the service from Mike the owner was impeccable. There is a lot of love in this place!

Fantastic, locally owned bbq. Visited for lunch today and the brisket and jalapeño sausage are legit awesome. Mac N Cheese also super yummy, and plenty of other choices to try on the menu. Make sure to have a massive chocolate chip cookie before you leave. This place is great and we will visit again very soon!
Some of the best BBQ and sides in Dallas.  Looking forward to many more visits in the future.  Try to save room for dessert if you can which is easier said then done.
Excellent!
Great service. Good food
The brisket had a mild but distinctive smoke flavor. Moist, yet not much bark. The brussel sprouts cooked with craisins and flavorful pot liquor were very good.
Food was delicious, drinks were great & the desserts were the best! The bar staff last night definitely kept up with us.
nice layout  good service, good desserts, decent bbq, sides where ok as well. Not a bbq destination like some places in the metroplex but if you have a taste for bbq and are in the area, it is good.

I tried this place for the first time. It's really really good bbq, I had the moist brisket, pork burnt ends, ribs and pulled pork. You could tell the Pit Master takes pride in his work, all the meats were spectacular. The sides were also …

Good barbecue and pretty good prices. The fries and the mac and cheese were great also. The brisket had a little bit too much fat and a very strong bark. The bark was a little bit too strong for my liking but still good food.

I went once it was good. It's kinda expensive but it is bbq. I don't get why people are surprised the prices are posted. I like the quality of everything. People are complaining about how fatty the wagyu is. That's wagyu that's what it's …

This place is AMAZING!  The people are incredibly nice, they treated my senior parents like royalty.  The food was unbelievable!  Great sides and BBQ is wonderful!  Hands down best BBQ in Dallas. We will 100% be back.
The brisket and turkey were amazing and the fries were made to order! Service was quick and prices were reasonable. Will come back!
Food tested great and the staff was extremely friendly. Thank you for a good first experience!
Brisket is to die for. I thoroughly enjoyed the wagyu sausage as well. Great place for a casual lunch or a drink on the weekend. Oh, don't leave without a giant chocolate chunk cookie! Yes!

We came to this restaurant for lunch. we heard about this restaurant from quite a few people.  Well, it was a winning. we were warmly welcomed by the staff members  and we felt very good. The meal was great. We loved this spot very much and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Recommended.
Friendly people. Great food. They have a pastry team and fresh baked goods as well, very uncommon and I'll be back. I had the Governor sandwich and it was easily two meals!

Thank you Nathan for preparing our food it was great your suggestions was spot on. Nathan the PitBoss a day his staff is awesome. You have a choice to eat outside they have a full bar. We even got a tour of the largest BBQ pit i have ever seen. The brusselsprouts are off the chain
This is the best BBQ I have ever had. The mac and cheese and the apple cider cole slaw are AMAZING!

First BBQ meal back in the Dallas/Fort worth metroplex was a hit. OAK’D BBQ is definitely a great spot. Atmosphere is incredible and the attention to detail is present from the decor all the way through to the many choices of food and …
Really enjoyed the food here!!!  The Chef is second to none for me!!! Traveled from Michigan to this place...and my taste buds are still thanking me! LOL
Amazing!!! Great service everything is homemade including the fabulous desserts! If you go I recommend the banana bread OMG it’s the bomb I’ve never had anything better! You won’t regret
Thought the food was great but it was a little pricy. A 1 meat-1 side plate was $14 and a light beer was $5. The sausage is great though so there’s a good chance I’ll be back.
The food was awesome but it was too expensive. There is too much great BBQ in the area at a much better price point. Sorry Oak'd I really wanted to love you.

Very nice location and excellent ambiance to the spot. Ribs, brisket and pulled pork were good flavor, moist and well seasoned. Sides were acceptable although I was not blown away by the mac and cheese. The apple cider coleslaw was better …
Wagu brisket was awesome
Very good BBQ and prices are reasonable.  Music is excellent.
One of the best BBQ restaurants I've had. Great environment and friendly staff. Jalepeno cheddar sausage was amazing. I'm from Colorado and would make a trip back just to eat here.
Very good bbq. Thx

Absolutely great BBQ. My favorite in Dallas. I own the Concierge Network in the hotels and we send guests there regularly and always hear positive feedback. Everything from the ribs to stuffed jalapenos to desert is great. Good live music and full bar as well.
Amazing selection of sides and desserts.
Great smoked bbq. Ribs slide off the bone and the brisket melts in your mouth.  Glad I found this spot.

I don't want to come down too hard here as my visit was a few weeks back in their first week of operation. What I would say is that the Wagyu Brisket definitely missed the mark, it was on the dry side. Also the beans were not top notch. To …

Was disappointed. We had the Wagyu, Prime Brisket and Smoked Turkey. The Prime Brisket and Wagyu that we received were almost1/2 fat. Sorry but if I am gonna pay that kinda money, I don’t want all that fat

Fantastic new BBQ place in Dallas! Our party of five tried all the meats and most of the sides and we loved it all.  The Wagyu beef brisket was so tender to cut and melted in our mouths. The chicken had great smoky flavor. The pork butt was …
Everything was great, will be back

I really hoped to give y'all 5 stars.  Your meats are great I ordered point (fatty or moist in Texas)but received flat which was somewhat dry which is unusual for Wagyu.  The SRF Wagyu we use in comps has always been very moist.  I'd like …

Went to Oak’d BBQ today for lunch.   I was excited to try it.  Boy was I disappointed.  I had sliced brisket and Mac and cheese and my friend had brisket and 2 sides plus 2 sodas and  our bill was over $60.  I had no idea it would be that …

Great BBQ in a convenient location. I’ve eaten at most of the top BBQ places in Dallas and while I wouldn’t consider this #1 it’s certainly top 5 and a place I’ll go back to. Pork ribs, brisket, Brussels sprouts and cauliflower were all fantastic.

I ate lunch there today and I must say I was very unimpressed. The brisket I ordered, and was very expensive, was almost all fat.  High price to pay for fat.  The beans did not taste completely cooked and the greens were ok.  All in All it was very expensive for what you get and not very good BBQ.  I will not be back.

I've had a lot of barbecue in my life and this is definitely one of my favorites. The Duroc Pork Butt paired with the balsamic roasted Brussels Sprouts was one of the best dishes I've ever had. It went great with an Allen's Old Fashioned …

Wow, what a great experience. Food and service was outstanding. The Wagyu brisket was extremely tasty and the steak fries and Mac and cheese were delicious. Wish I would have left room for dessert, because they all looked wonderful. All made fresh daily.
So much more than your average BBQ restaurant. Highly recommend the desserts!
The Q was fantastic - Only reason I gave you all 4 stars is that I was charged for pickles?  Seriously - charging for pickles is a bit much...

Charged wrong price on brisket, brisket was tough, burnt end seasoning was a little off. Pickles and jalapeno sausage were great. Service was good. It is early and I am sure they will work things out.

On their menu, I tried the sandwich and some lovin, which was delicious! It had pulled pork, jalapeño cheese sausage with bacon and cole slaw. Their steak fries and mac n cheese are great too! Sauces were good as well. The pit master, …
Tried ‘The sandwich with some lovein’ it was great! Can’t wait to try some more.
Tried this place before with a friend and I am obsessed ever since. I like the good mood and delightful food and beverages. 5 stars from me.
Wow this is a 5+star BBQ restaurant. The jalapeño cheddar cheese sausage is excellent. You won't leave disappointed.
Loved the wagyu brisket! Best bbq ive even had.
Great food and awesome service! We definitely will be back! Great prices compared to others

First visit. We ordered a Brisket sandwich and one of the jalapeño cheddar sausages. We also had red skinned potato salad. I will start with the sausage. One word says it all.... AMAZING. The brisket sandwich had good flavor without any BBQ …

Went here for the first time after seeing it on Instagram. I’ve been seeing it everywhere online and had to check it out. Here are my thoughts... wow WOW was blown away. Must try: wagu brisket, sausage, baked potato and the s’mores pie. …
The wagyu brisket was fatty and flavorless. The turkey wasn’t as bad, and the apple pie was alright as well. It’s messed up my stomach

So glad I live within walking distance of here so I can burn off the food! The serving sizes for an individual are amazing. The meats are the true star of the show.  This was my first time here and they did not disappoint. They have great …

Got to try a great sample of meats and sides...prime brisket, wagyu brisket, jalapeno cheddar sausage,  pork ribs,  and burnt ends...Mac & cheese, steak fries and brussel sprouts.  Great set up with 3 offset smokers...and live music on the patio...  Had a great meal/experience today and will be back!!
Had this for lunch just now the portions are ginormous and the desserts looked really good. If I didn’t eat like a bird I’d definitely had gotten some. I thoroughly enjoyed it!

This place needs to get their information straight. Their hours are inconsistent on their website/google page with what is up on the door.  Their phone number is also incorrect on the google page and when I called the number on their …

This place opens at 4:30p for dinner. We walked in and were told to wait until 5:00p to order because they weren’t ready. Cooks and servers looked disorganized. Cooks and servers were not wearing masks properly either. They had them on as chin straps.

Got food to go for the office on the opening day.  Meat was DELICIOUS, hello meat sweats, and the desserts were to die for.  I'm not a cheesecake fan but there's was so good.  Going again today and will hopefully get somethings that were already sold out of.

Prices are bit high, especially the side dishes.  I ordered the 1/2 pound of waygu brisket and was surprised at how dried out it was.  I'll probably give it another try but so far it's all just mediocre flavors.
Wagyu brisket for good prices; sides aplenty; nice indoor and outdoor setup with a nice bar area.
Everything was delicious😍👌

We ate at Oak’d for the first time today. I consider myself a “bbq snob” and their food was delicious. The meat was cooked perfectly and was smokey and tender. Our favorite by far were the beef ribs and the jalapeño sausage. Brisket and …
Amazing stuff!  Wagyu beef from Rosewood Ranch, and the sides are the best of any BBQ place, hands down.  Coleslaw is tossed to order and biscuits are hot out of the oven.  Must try!
Wow, what a surprise this place is.  Cuts of meat are fantastic and all the sides had great flavor.  The pastry chef made for some difficult choices.  We recommend the s’mores pie!
High quality, we loved everything we ate. We'll be back.
